  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "Climbing crag located on the eastern shore of Norrviken. The south-facing cliffs, 5–12 m high, are at the end of Solängsvägen and angled towards the lake, about 600 m from its southern tip.\n\nA number of sport, boulder, and trad routes exist here, though some trad lines may require a bit of love in the form of a steel brush. Many new sport routes have been cleaned up, and a general refresh has been made. Most sport routes have top anchors. The newly developed Järnpinneväggen features the crag's finest routes, \"Chippad av Staten\" and \"En månad av frihet\". Due to many routes being relatively short and intense, they can often feel challenging to onsight. Recently, several bolted lines have been added in the lower grade for those looking to learn to lead.\n\nThe rock is quality granite and is recommended for those living in the area.",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:tornskogsklippan"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Overview",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tornskogsklippan"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The climbing crag is located on the eastern shore of Norrviken. The south-facing cliffs, ranging from 5 to 12 m, are situated at the end of Solängsvägen, angled towards the lake, approximately 600 m from its southern tip.\n\nA variety of sport, boulder, and trad routes can be found here, although some trad lines may need a little love in the form of a steel brush. Many new sport routes have been cleaned up, and a general refresh has been done. Most sport routes feature top anchors. The newly developed Järnpinneväggen hosts the best routes on the crag, \"Chippad av Staten\" and \"En månad av frihet\". Due to the relatively short and intense nature of many routes, they can often feel hard to onsight. Recently, several bolted routes have been added in the lower grade range for those looking to learn to lead.\n\nThe rock is good quality granite and is recommended for those living in the area.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tornskogsklippan"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tornskogsklippan"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Drive along Frestavägen. Turn left towards Solängen. Continue as far as you can into the residential area, and the crag will be visible on your right. Follow the path straight ahead if you intend to swim. Another option to access from above is to bypass the left turn onto Solängen, continue straight, then turn left onto Båtsmansvägen, turn left again at Trestegsvägen, and then enter Vaxmoravägen. Park a couple of hundred meters on the right side before the no-parking sign.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:tornskogsklippan"
            ]
          }
        },
        "oversikt": {
